Argentina international, Paulo Dybala, has made a transfer U-turn, amid interest from Premier League clubs. Dybala is now willing to consider a move to the Premier League, opening the door to the possibility he could replace forward Cristiano Ronaldo at Manchester United. The 28-year-old has been without a club since leaving Juventus at the end of his contract this summer. His preference had been to remain in Italy, with Inter Milan widely considered front-runners for his signature. However, according to Sky Sport Italia, no offers have materialised from Serie A clubs and Dybala is now ready to evaluate offers from England and Spain instead. Dybala would prefer a move to the Premier League over La Liga and both Man United and Arsenal are believed to have already made contact with his agent. Man Unitedâ€™s interest in Dybala is now expected to ramp up in the coming days should the Red Devils allow Ronaldo to leave Old Trafford.